        <h1 class="hero-title">Cordyceps</h1>
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">The Energy Mushroom</p>
        <p>Cordyceps (<em>Cordyceps militaris</em>) has been used for centuries in Tibetan and Chinese traditional practices, valued for its role in supporting endurance and stamina. Sherpas in the Himalayas have used it for generations during long climbs at altitude.</p>
        <p>Today, it is one of the most studied functional mushrooms for cellular energy. It works at a cellular level, supporting the systems that produce ATP, the molecule your cells use as fuel.</p>
